## ❓ Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Is this RAT legal?**  
A: The tool itself is legal for authorized testing. Using it on systems you don't own is illegal.

**Q: Does it work on Windows 11?**  
A: Yes, it works on all Windows versions from XP to 11.

**Q: Can it bypass antivirus?**  
A: The standard version is detected by most AVs. Obfuscation can help avoid detection temporarily.

**Q: What ports does it use?**  
A: Default ports are configurable during setup.

**Q: Is the source code available?**  
A: Various versions of the source code have been publicly available.

**Q: Can I use dynamic DNS?**  
A: Yes, it supports DDNS services for dynamic IPs.

